properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 6 at 3:11AM MST until January 6 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...STRONG WIND GUSTS TO 65 MPH LIKELY THIS MORNING AND AFTERNOON.
GUSTY WINDS WILL CONTINUE THROUGH TUESDAY MORNING...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect until 5 PM MST this afternoon.

* WHAT...West winds 40 to 50 mph with gusts of 55 to 65 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Eastern Laramie County Wyoming and Kimball County
Nebraska.

* WHEN...Until 5pm this evening

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will
develop on North South highways. High profile vehicles will be
at an increased risk of blowovers. Secure loose outdoor items.
Trees and powerlines may be damaged.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON
